'''第10太陽週期'''是從1755年開始紀錄太陽黑子以來的第10個[[太陽週期|太陽週期]]<ref name="Kane">Kane, R.P. (2002). "[http://www.springerlink.com/content/qtq52nl8vtq7w2t6/ Some Implications Using the Group Sunspot Number Reconstruction] {{Webarchive|url=https://archive.is/20121204174904/http://www.springerlink.com/content/qtq52nl8vtq7w2t6/ |date=2012-12-04 }}". ''Solar Physics'' '''205(2)''', 383-401.</ref><ref name=SpaceToday>{{cite web | title=The Sun: Did You Say the Sun Has Spots? | url=http://www.spacetoday.org/SolSys/Sun/Sunspots.html | publisher=Space Today Online | accessdate=12 August 2010 | archive-date=2017-07-22 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170722010544/http://www.spacetoday.org/SolSys/Sun/Sunspots.html | dead-url=no }}</ref>，這個週期開始於1855年12月，結束於1867年3月，持續了11.3年。最大平滑黑子數(超過12個月期間的黑子月平均數值)為97.3，最小的數值為2.5<ref name="SIDC Monthly Smoothed Sunspot Number">SIDC Monthly Smoothed Sunspot Number. "[http://sidc.oma.be/sunspot-data/] {{Wayback|url=http://sidc.oma.be/sunspot-data/ |date=20140328111426 }}"</ref>，在這個週期內總共約有406天沒有黑子<ref name="Spotless Days">Spotless Days. "[http://spaceweather.com/glossary/spotlessdays.htm?PHPSESSID=dli444kmrjgre0rjq6l86fv144] {{Wayback|url=http://spaceweather.com/glossary/spotlessdays.htm?PHPSESSID=dli444kmrjgre0rjq6l86fv144 |date=20160303185014 }}"</ref><ref name="What's Wrong with the Sun? (Nothing)">What's Wrong with the Sun? (Nothing) more information: Spotless Days. "[http://science.nasa.gov/headlines/y2008/11jul_solarcycleupdate.htm] {{Wayback|url=http://science.nasa.gov/headlines/y2008/11jul_solarcycleupdate.htm |date=20080714032353 }}"</ref><ref name="Solaemon's Spotless Days Page">Solaemon's Spotless Days Page. "[http://users.telenet.be/j.janssens/Spotless/Spotless.html] {{Wayback|url=http://users.telenet.be/j.janssens/Spotless/Spotless.html |date=20170722234836 }}"</ref>。

== 1859年太陽風暴 ==
{{main|1859年太陽風暴}}
[[Image:Carrington_Richard_sunspots_1859.jpg|thumb]]描繪的1859年9月1日的太陽黑子。]]

在1859年9月1日和2日，發生了紀錄上最大的[[磁暴|地磁風暴]]，全球各地都看見了[[極光|極光]]。值得一提的是在[[加勒比|加勒比]]都非常的明亮，以致[[落磯山|落磯山]]當地金礦的礦工都被驚醒，以為是早晨來臨了，都開始準備早餐<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.sciam.com/article.cfm?id=timeline-the-1859-solar-superstorm |title="Timeline: The 1859 Solar Superstorm". |access-date=2010-09-14 |archive-date=2008-11-21 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081121022234/http://www.sciam.com/article.cfm?id=timeline-the-1859-solar-superstorm |dead-url=no }}</ref>，或是'''卡靈頓事件'''<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://science.nasa.gov/headlines/y2009/21jan_severespaceweather.htm?list5029 |title="NASA — Severe Space Weather". |access-date=2010-09-14 |archive-date=2009-04-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090404064739/http://science.nasa.gov/headlines/y2009/21jan_severespaceweather.htm?list5029 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="Odenwald" />。

越洋聯繫歐洲和北美州的[[電報|電報]]系統失效<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.space.com/scienceastronomy/mystery_monday_031027.html |title="The Great Storm: Solar Tempest of 1859 Revealed". |access-date=2010-09-14 |archive-date=2003-12-02 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20031202023825/http://www.space.com/scienceastronomy/mystery_monday_031027.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>，電報塔架發出火花，電報紙也都自發性的著火。儘管電源供應是關閉的，但有些電報系統似乎繼續發送和接收郵件。

從1859年8月28日直到9月2日，在太陽上觀測到大量的[[太陽黑子|太陽黑子]]和[[閃焰|閃焰]]，就在9月1日的中午之前，英國天文學家[[理查·卡靈頓|理查·卡靈頓]]觀察到一個[[1859年太陽風暴|最大的閃焰]]<ref name="Odenwald">{{Cite web |url=http://www.sciam.com/article.cfm?id=bracing-for-a-solar-superstorm |title="Bracing the Satellite Infrastructure for a Solar Superstorm". |access-date=2010-09-14 |archive-date=2008-11-17 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081117113249/http://www.sciam.com/article.cfm?id=bracing-for-a-solar-superstorm |dead-url=no }}</ref>，它造成大質量的[[日冕物質拋射|日冕物質拋射]](CME)，經過18小時就直接抵達地球。值得注意的是通常要3至4天才會抵達地球，他會如次快速的移動是因為之前的CME已經將道路清除乾淨了<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.sciam.com/slideshow.cfm?id=bracing-for-a-solar-superstorm&thumbs=horizontal&photo_id=70B030E1-F2BB-B582-B5EC43C9721FE03B |title="Bracing the Satellite Infrastructure for a Solar Superstorm", slide #2. |access-date=2010-09-14 |archive-date=2009-04-04 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090404063938/http://www.sciam.com/slideshow.cfm?id=bracing-for-a-solar-superstorm&thumbs=horizontal&photo_id=70B030E1-F2BB-B582-B5EC43C9721FE03B |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

